    "body": "Problem: It is possible (and documented in `:h vim.pack`) that plugin's\r\n  `src` uses \"insteadOf\" Git config. In that case comparing it directly\r\n  to repo's `origin` will error.\r\n\r\nSolution: Add extra check that lockfile's `src` is not equal to repo's\r\n  `origin` when taking Git's \"insteadOf\" into account.\r\n\r\n  However, still report the original lockfile's `src` in the\r\n  `:checkhealth` output, as it seems to be a clearer indication of what\r\n  actually is wrong.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nFix #38387",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-20T21:40:45Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38393#discussion_r2966798771"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/38393"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/2966798771"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The code above calls `failed_git_cmd()` if the command fails. Shouldn't it be the same here? However, on my machine, `git ls-remote --get-url` only fails if no argument is provided and works even outside a git repository. Might it be better to `assert(ok)` here then?",
            "commit_id": "dd12439ba0363094b38b99ff2ff875bd315092d9",
            "created_at": "2026-03-20T16:39:20Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -137,12 +137,16 @@ local function check_plugin_lock_data(plug_name, lock_data)\n   if not has_origin then\n     return failed_git_cmd(plug_name, plug_path)\n   elseif lock_data.src ~= origin then\n-    health.error(\n-      ('Plugin %s has not expected source\\n'):format(name_str)\n-        .. ('Expected: %s\\nActual:   %s\\n'):format(lock_data.src, origin)\n-        .. 'Delete `src` lockfile entry (do not create trailing comma) and '\n-        .. 'restart Nvim to regenerate lockfile data'\n-    )\n+    -- Check if lockfile source relies on \"insteadOf\" Git config\n+    local ok, src_resolved = git_cmd({ 'ls-remote', '--get-url', lock_data.src }, plug_path)\n+    if not (ok and src_resolved == origin) then",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38393#discussion_r2966798771",
            "id": 2966798771,
            "line": 142,
            "node_id": "PRRC_kwDOAPphoM6w1cGz",
